00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,140
 Now I wanna talk a little bit about how you or us,

2
00:00:04,140 --> 00:00:06,520
 we can create our own tags

3
00:00:06,520 --> 00:00:08,960
 and then use them throughout our markup.

4
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:13,000
 So what is this whole thing about creating new tags?

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:15,600
 Well, programmers hate to repeat themselves.

6
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:17,960
 It's just from the third week

7
00:00:17,960 --> 00:00:19,360
 of learning how to write software,

8
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:23,000
 it's all about don't repeat yourself, D-R-Y.

9
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,680
 And that's because if you write the same code over and over,

10
00:00:26,680 --> 00:00:29,220
 especially if there are tiny changes in that code

11
00:00:29,220 --> 00:00:32,820
 or little like if then else's, it really causes errors.

12
00:00:32,820 --> 00:00:34,520
 And if you have a bunch of code,

13
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:36,920
 and by now you've seen this in this course,

14
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:40,140
 if you cut and paste and make small changes

15
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:41,800
 and then paste and make small changes

16
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:46,120
 and paste and make small changes, it's convenient.

17
00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:48,420
 You're repeating yourself and then making changes.

18
00:00:48,420 --> 00:00:49,720
 But what if you started with a bug

19
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:50,880
 and all that stuff, you paste it,

20
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:54,140
 or you find a bug later and now you got 40 places

21
00:00:54,140 --> 00:00:55,740
 and you gotta make the same tiny change.

22
00:00:55,740 --> 00:00:57,520
 It's really frustrating.

23
00:00:57,520 --> 00:01:01,240
 And this just means that a big part of software

24
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:03,560
 is how to avoid repeating ourselves.

25
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:07,300
 Things like functions with parameters,

26
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:09,780
 object-oriented approaches with base classes

27
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:13,080
 that we're extending, the class-based views in Django

28
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:14,480
 versus just function views.

29
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:16,720
 I mean, the function views are simpler

30
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:17,640
 and easier to understand.

31
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:20,440
 Class-based views are beautiful and elegant,

32
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:22,200
 but hard to understand.

33
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:26,160
 Like templates, like the navigation that you've been building.

34
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:28,600
 It would say extends baseboostrap.html.

35
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:33,600
 That's a way to not put the same navigation tech HTML

36
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:34,720
 on every page.

37
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:39,040
 And like the percent URL, you can change the remap URLs

38
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:42,160
 and urls.py and not have to make changes in your templates.

39
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:45,380
 Again, we don't like to repeat ourselves.

40
00:01:45,380 --> 00:01:49,240
 So what we've been doing up to this point

41
